JEDDAH: Saudi Arabia’s General Entertainment Authority, in cooperation with WWE, has announced that the WWE King and Queen of the Ring event will be held at Jeddah Superdome, the world’s largest freestanding dome, on Saturday, May 27. For the latest updates, follow us on Twitter @ArabNewsSport It will be the first King of the Ring premium live event to be held since 2015 and the first crowning of a queen since the inaugural Queen’s Crown Tournament which took place at WWE Crown Jewel in Riyadh in 2021. More details on WWE King and Queen of the Ring will be announced in the coming weeks.